name: 6. Wood Boss No More
description:
"It's funny the things you think of when your world is about to be annihilated. Wet this down, hide this under here, throw everything off the porch. Take the chainsaw somewhere safe was not one of them. Looking at the scorched plastic and metal, in all its German engineered glory, all I could hear was my Mum only days before telling me to take the tools home from the job I was doing. "But I'm only going to come back and finish it tomorrow". Sometimes life will go to great lengths to make you eat your words. Always take the tools home."

Photography by Jay Moon, during the Australian wildfires; November 2019.
#6 of 15.
All funds generated go toward the ongoing recovery.
